00:18:42,202 --> 00:18:44,172
- Director Kang spun it.
- Happy Special.

533
00:18:44,572 --> 00:18:46,442
(Nervous)

534
00:18:46,672 --> 00:18:48,002
It's impossible to predict.

535
00:18:49,242 --> 00:18:51,441
(Extreme Wilderness on a Deserted Island)

536
00:18:51,442 --> 00:18:54,042
(Open Sea Fishing Operation)

537
00:18:54,242 --> 00:18:56,781
(Impossible to sleep, No Sleep for 2 Days)

538
00:18:56,782 --> 00:18:59,522
(Fight Cold With Cold, Real Winter)

539
00:19:00,452 --> 00:19:02,952
(They must avoid anything difficult.)

540
00:19:03,422 --> 00:19:05,792
(While the staff members hold their breath and concentrate)

541
00:19:06,492 --> 00:19:07,861
- It's not bad.
- It's not bad.

542
00:19:07,862 --> 00:19:09,691
- It's bad.
- Happy Special.

543
00:19:09,692 --> 00:19:10,891
Look.

544
00:19:10,892 --> 00:19:12,662
- No.
- No, not that one.

545
00:19:12,832 --> 00:19:15,101
- We're doomed.
- No.

546
00:19:15,102 --> 00:19:16,871
(2 Days 1 Night)

547
00:19:16,872 --> 00:19:18,871
(Extreme Wilderness on a Deserted Island, Happy Special...)

548
00:19:18,872 --> 00:19:21,441
(It stopped.)

549
00:19:21,442 --> 00:19:22,972
We got Drawing Groups.

550
00:19:23,312 --> 00:19:24,342
(Screaming with joy)

551
00:19:24,772 --> 00:19:26,981
(Drawing Groups is picked.)

552
00:19:26,982 --> 00:19:28,482
We got it.

553
00:19:29,152 --> 00:19:30,981
It's all thanks to you.

554
00:19:30,982 --> 00:19:32,422
(Very excited)

555
00:19:33,222 --> 00:19:34,921
- We will work hard.
- Yes.

556
00:19:34,922 --> 00:19:36,051
(In despair)

557
00:19:36,052 --> 00:19:37,292
The father of 2 Days 1 Night.

558
00:19:37,692 --> 00:19:39,021
Among so many slots...

559
00:19:39,022 --> 00:19:40,462
(Thank you, Director.)

560
00:19:41,292 --> 00:19:42,832
The chances were so low.

561
00:19:43,662 --> 00:19:45,331
- The chances were so low.
- This is insane.

562
00:19:45,332 --> 00:19:47,678
- The next slot was a nightmare.
- We would've been doomed.

563
00:19:47,702 --> 00:19:50,371
You know what's funny? Only those over here look unhappy.

564
00:19:50,372 --> 00:19:51,731
- Everyone else is happy.
- Right.

565
00:19:51,732 --> 00:19:54,101
Imagine coming to work at 6pm.

566
00:19:54,102 --> 00:19:56,511
(Those who look happy at the thought of coming to work in the evening)

567
00:19:56,512 --> 00:19:58,472
- Aren't we on the same team?
- Okay.

568
00:19:58,612 --> 00:20:00,381
We need to work hard.

569
00:20:00,382 --> 00:20:03,382
The trip you picked called Drawing Groups.

570
00:20:03,652 --> 00:20:05,681
We will do our best to make it happen...

571
00:20:05,682 --> 00:20:07,621
- as early as possible.
- Gosh.

572
00:20:07,622 --> 00:20:10,392
Please coordinate it with the upcoming World Cup.

573
00:20:10,492 --> 00:20:12,521
Thank you for your hard work, everyone.

574
00:20:12,522 --> 00:20:15,021
- Let's go to the base camp now.
- Okay.

575
00:20:15,022 --> 00:20:16,731
Thank you, Director.

576
00:20:16,732 --> 00:20:18,362
Thank you.

577
00:20:19,062 --> 00:20:21,161
I'm so glad that we didn't get 24 Hours Without Sleep.

578
00:20:21,162 --> 00:20:22,502
That sounds really difficult.

579
00:20:23,232 --> 00:20:25,671
If it takes place soon,

580
00:20:25,672 --> 00:20:27,372
won't it be within a month?

581
00:20:28,072 --> 00:20:30,841
Please take into account that...

582
00:20:30,842 --> 00:20:32,742
we have to make prior visits and hold meetings.

583
00:20:33,112 --> 00:20:35,441
The person who came up with the idea should join the visit.

584
00:20:35,442 --> 00:20:36,551
Whose idea was it?

585
00:20:36,552 --> 00:20:37,711
- DinDin's.
- It was DinDin's idea.

586
00:20:37,712 --> 00:20:39,552
No, it was Se Yoon's idea.

587
00:20:40,082 --> 00:20:42,891
My idea was getting off work on the same day.

588
00:20:42,892 --> 00:20:44,791
- I will make sure to send DinDin.
- Okay.

589
00:20:44,792 --> 00:20:45,822
All right.

590
00:20:46,062 --> 00:20:47,391
While making plans,

591
00:20:47,392 --> 00:20:48,762
contact me from time to time.

592
00:20:49,262 --> 00:20:50,462
If you get confused.

593
00:20:51,632 --> 00:20:52,801
What do we do?

594
00:20:52,802 --> 00:20:55,502
(Their evening in Chuncheon is coming to an end.)

595
00:20:55,702 --> 00:20:57,171
We're finally indoors now.

596
00:20:57,172 --> 00:20:58,371
(After spending the day outdoors, they arrive at the warm base camp.)

597
00:20:58,372 --> 00:21:00,841
- This is where we rest...
- Excuse me.

598
00:21:00,842 --> 00:21:02,742
- What's this?
- What?

599
00:21:03,072 --> 00:21:04,952
- We're in the military.
- What? It looks nice.

600
00:21:05,712 --> 00:21:07,242
Report the current headcount.

601
00:21:08,442 --> 00:21:09,812
Do we have to sit like this?

602
00:21:10,212 --> 00:21:11,912
Exactly. You should practice.

603
00:21:12,152 --> 00:21:13,521
Why is your hair so long?

604
00:21:13,522 --> 00:21:15,151
(Absorbed in recalling memories of the military)

605
00:21:15,152 --> 00:21:16,751
- What's wrong with you?
- Check his nails.

606
00:21:16,752 --> 00:21:17,752
Hello.

607
00:21:17,753 --> 00:21:18,821
You're trying to pick a fight.

608
00:21:18,822 --> 00:21:19,822
- Hey.
- He gained weight.

609
00:21:19,823 --> 00:21:21,238
There must be something. What is it?

610
00:21:21,262 --> 00:21:23,361
- What is it?
- Everyone.

611
00:21:23,362 --> 00:21:25,132
At ease. Freeze.

612
00:21:25,762 --> 00:21:27,062
- Don't come near us.
- At ease.

613
00:21:27,602 --> 00:21:28,602
- What?
- All right.

614
00:21:28,603 --> 00:21:30,801
They came in so suddenly.

615
00:21:30,802 --> 00:21:32,671
It's scary to see people in black come in so suddenly.

616
00:21:32,672 --> 00:21:33,771
It seems ominous.

617
00:21:33,772 --> 00:21:35,172
- Everyone.
- Yes?

618
00:21:35,342 --> 00:21:36,472
What is it?

619
00:21:37,012 --> 00:21:38,641
I will explain Sleeping Indoors or Outdoors...

620
00:21:38,642 --> 00:21:40,212
in advance.

621
00:21:40,582 --> 00:21:42,311
- In advance?
- What's going on?

622
00:21:42,312 --> 00:21:43,911
We prepared tonight's Sleeping Indoors or Outdoors...

623
00:21:43,912 --> 00:21:45,552
for the New Year.

624
00:21:46,052 --> 00:21:48,221
It's called I Will Show You How I Changed Completely.

625
00:21:48,222 --> 00:21:50,292
(I Will Show You How I Changed Completely)

626
00:21:50,822 --> 00:21:52,792
(What could it be?)

627
00:21:52,922 --> 00:21:54,022
Based on the number...

628
00:21:54,662 --> 00:21:57,191
of members who fail to achieve...

629
00:21:57,192 --> 00:21:59,732
their New Year's resolutions,

630
00:22:00,262 --> 00:22:02,571
you will draw lots to decide who sleeps outdoors.

631
00:22:02,572 --> 00:22:04,231
What are my New Year resolutions?

632
00:22:04,232 --> 00:22:06,178
- To each of you...
- I don't have any resolutions.

633
00:22:06,202 --> 00:22:07,202
I don't have any.

634
00:22:07,203 --> 00:22:09,171
I live only for today.

635
00:22:09,172 --> 00:22:10,541
- All right.
- We live only for today.

636
00:22:10,542 --> 00:22:11,571
Did the staff decide...

637
00:22:11,572 --> 00:22:12,911
- our New Year resolutions?
- Yes.

638
00:22:12,912 --> 00:22:14,142
- That's ridiculous.
- What?

639
00:22:14,412 --> 00:22:15,481
What?

640
00:22:15,482 --> 00:22:16,711
I don't have any resolutions.

641
00:22:16,712 --> 00:22:17,911
Why would you decide for me?

642
00:22:17,912 --> 00:22:20,321
I will announce your New Year resolutions...

643
00:22:20,322 --> 00:22:22,652
that you must accomplish.

644
00:22:22,992 --> 00:22:24,252
A moment ago,

645
00:22:24,622 --> 00:22:26,361
- I asked you to jump.
- What?

646
00:22:26,362 --> 00:22:29,491
It was a mission to measure DinDin's abilities.

647
00:22:29,492 --> 00:22:31,061
- What?
- What do you mean?

648
00:22:31,062 --> 00:22:32,292
(My abilities?)

649
00:22:32,462 --> 00:22:33,982
- Is it here?
- Joon, can you do this?

650
00:22:34,132 --> 00:22:36,232
What?

651
00:22:37,902 --> 00:22:39,071
It's the Sargent jump test.

652
00:22:39,072 --> 00:22:40,278
(The Sargent jump test that requires vertical jumping)

653
00:22:40,302 --> 00:22:42,242
(Starting with Seon Ho who's tall)

654
00:22:47,312 --> 00:22:48,782
He hit higher than that.

655
00:22:49,412 --> 00:22:51,182
- You did well.
- What was that about?

656
00:22:51,412 --> 00:22:52,521
- Let him borrow it.
- Seriously.

657
00:22:52,522 --> 00:22:53,881
- DinDin, try it.
- Do you practice jumping?

658
00:22:53,882 --> 00:22:56,192
- I jumped, and...
- DinDin is a man of basketball.

659
00:22:57,052 --> 00:22:58,651
DinDin, try to hit the red.

660
00:22:58,652 --> 00:22:59,922
My knees hurt.

661
00:23:01,722 --> 00:23:02,891
- Seriously?
- Are you serious?

662
00:23:02,892 --> 00:23:03,991
- He's lying.
- Really?

663
00:23:03,992 --> 00:23:05,031
No.

664
00:23:05,032 --> 00:23:07,032
DinDin, aren't you planning...

665
00:23:07,502 --> 00:23:09,602
to grow in 2026?

666
00:23:09,832 --> 00:23:12,401
You will succeed if you jump higher...

667
00:23:12,402 --> 00:23:14,071
than what you did before.

668
00:23:14,072 --> 00:23:15,101
- What?
- My gosh.

669
00:23:15,102 --> 00:23:16,811
DinDin jumped carelessly a moment ago.

670
00:23:16,812 --> 00:23:18,171
You kept telling me to jump,

671
00:23:18,172 --> 00:23:19,541
but I didn't want to.

672
00:23:19,542 --> 00:23:21,682
I was like, "Why is he insisting?"

673
00:23:22,182 --> 00:23:23,711
(DinDin's New Year resolution)

674
00:23:23,712 --> 00:23:25,311
(The Sargent jump test, breaking his own record)

675
00:23:25,312 --> 00:23:27,321
DinDin did a good job.

676
00:23:27,322 --> 00:23:28,381
He got lucky.

677
00:23:28,382 --> 00:23:30,698
- What are our resolutions?
- Is there anything we can do?

678
00:23:30,722 --> 00:23:32,021
Lee Joon.

679
00:23:32,022 --> 00:23:34,922
Joon, you toss and turn often at night.

680
00:23:35,322 --> 00:23:37,802
- Is it falling asleep fast?
- While verification takes place,

681
00:23:38,162 --> 00:23:39,661
you must fall into a deep sleep.

682
00:23:39,662 --> 00:23:41,478
- How would you verify?
- He just has to sleep?

683
00:23:41,502 --> 00:23:43,531
What if I pretend to sleep?

684
00:23:43,532 --> 00:23:44,932
I could pretend to be asleep.

685
00:23:45,072 --> 00:23:46,671
- What if...
- There must be a way...

686
00:23:46,672 --> 00:23:48,432
- to verify your deep sleep.
- We'll verify.

687
00:23:48,502 --> 00:23:50,371
There must be a way. Yours isn't difficult either.

688
00:23:50,372 --> 00:23:52,112
Joon, try not to fall asleep.

689
00:23:52,642 --> 00:23:54,181
When ordered to fall asleep, he won't be able to.

690
00:23:54,182 --> 00:23:55,441
- For Jong Min...
- I would feel nervous.

691
00:23:55,442 --> 00:23:56,711
Right.

692
00:23:56,712 --> 00:23:59,012
- Your goal is becoming a dad.
- Right.

693
00:23:59,152 --> 00:24:00,382
What is this?

694
00:24:01,382 --> 00:24:03,142
- Here...
- Does he have to give birth here?

695
00:24:03,622 --> 00:24:04,822
Is this going to be aired?

696
00:24:05,552 --> 00:24:06,921
In front of the cameras...

697
00:24:06,922 --> 00:24:08,691
(Do what here?)

698
00:24:08,692 --> 00:24:10,261
- Are you out of your mind?
- What are you up to?

699
00:24:10,262 --> 00:24:11,262
(Flustered)

700
00:24:11,263 --> 00:24:12,561
- Are you out of your mind?
- What is this?

701
00:24:12,562 --> 00:24:14,402
Why would you show that to us?

702
00:24:14,632 --> 00:24:15,971
- All right.
- He must be out of his mind.

703
00:24:15,972 --> 00:24:18,302
How much will you show on TV?

704
00:24:18,802 --> 00:24:20,102
- All right.
- What on earth?

705
00:24:20,242 --> 00:24:22,442
- Okay.
- To train you as a good father,

706
00:24:22,872 --> 00:24:25,412
we'll give you children's books to read to a child.

707
00:24:25,572 --> 00:24:26,841
He's not allowed to stammer.

708
00:24:26,842 --> 00:24:27,842
Goodness.

709
00:24:27,843 --> 00:24:29,611
- Do I have to memorize something?
- For Jong Min...

710
00:24:29,612 --> 00:24:32,112
Does Jong Min have to read without knowing...

711
00:24:32,482 --> 00:24:33,822
- what the resolution is?
- Yes.

712
00:24:34,122 --> 00:24:35,581
"Red Bean Porridge and Grandma?"

713
00:24:35,582 --> 00:24:37,491
(He has no clue.)

714
00:24:37,492 --> 00:24:40,992
Seon Ho, for you to study what you struggle with the most,

715
00:24:41,322 --> 00:24:43,361
I'll give you books on countries and capital cities.

716
00:24:43,362 --> 00:24:44,491
That sounds hard.

717
00:24:44,492 --> 00:24:45,832
You'll be able to do it.

718
00:24:46,302 --> 00:24:48,161
You must pass the test to succeed.

719
00:24:48,162 --> 00:24:49,431
I stopped studying...

720
00:24:49,432 --> 00:24:50,771
since seventh grade.

721
00:24:50,772 --> 00:24:52,701
- For Se Yoon...
- Why am I last?

722
00:24:52,702 --> 00:24:53,872
Losing weight.

723
00:24:54,402 --> 00:24:56,472
- Your long-aspired project.
- What?

724
00:24:56,572 --> 00:24:57,811
- "Long-aspired project?"
- You're making him do a project?

725
00:24:57,812 --> 00:25:00,442
- Losing weight.
- You must lose weight to succeed.

726
00:25:01,712 --> 00:25:03,482
(Unbelievable)

727
00:25:03,882 --> 00:25:05,411
How can he lose weight right now?

728
00:25:05,412 --> 00:25:07,492
- Hurry and eat a tangerine now.
- For verification,

729
00:25:07,952 --> 00:25:10,292
we'll measure Se Yoon's current weight.

730
00:25:11,752 --> 00:25:13,022
It will go up to 140kg.

731
00:25:14,362 --> 00:25:15,592
I weigh 126.2kg.

732
00:25:16,062 --> 00:25:17,932
By tonight's verification time,

733
00:25:18,632 --> 00:25:21,101
- you have to lose 3kg.
- It's impossible to lose 3kg.

734
00:25:21,102 --> 00:25:23,201
- That's ridiculous.
- Lose 3kg?

735
00:25:23,202 --> 00:25:24,331
Are you telling him to disappear?

736
00:25:24,332 --> 00:25:26,141
You think it's easier for a fat person to lose weight?

737
00:25:26,142 --> 00:25:27,542
Does a pig lose weight that easily?

738
00:25:27,742 --> 00:25:29,101
How can you lose 3kg of fat?

739
00:25:29,102 --> 00:25:30,271
That's impossible.

740
00:25:30,272 --> 00:25:31,811
Three kilograms of fat is this big.

741
00:25:31,812 --> 00:25:33,488
He needs a sauna to lose that much weight.

742
00:25:33,512 --> 00:25:34,681
No, I'll be fine.

743
00:25:34,682 --> 00:25:36,952
- It's a bolt from the blue.
- This morning,

744
00:25:37,112 --> 00:25:38,381
I didn't even poop.

745
00:25:38,382 --> 00:25:39,581
(I didn't empty out my intestines.)

746
00:25:39,582 --> 00:25:41,181
Wait, you know what'd be more shocking?

747
00:25:41,182 --> 00:25:42,921
If he weighs 120kg after pooping,

748
00:25:42,922 --> 00:25:44,122
it would be unbelievable.

749
00:25:45,452 --> 00:25:48,091
(I will show you how I changed completely.)

750
00:25:48,092 --> 00:25:51,062
Later when Sleeping Indoors or Outdoors starts,

751
00:25:51,192 --> 00:25:52,732
- I'll come to verify.
- How...

752
00:25:52,962 --> 00:25:54,301
(Jong Min: Becoming a dad, Joon: Sleep deeply, )

753
00:25:54,302 --> 00:25:55,631
(Se Yoon: Losing weight, DinDin: Jumping high, )

754
00:25:55,632 --> 00:25:56,902
(Seon Ho: Gaining knowledge)

755
00:25:57,902 --> 00:26:00,172
- I'll go and lose weight.
- Good luck, Se Yoon.

756
00:26:00,972 --> 00:26:03,142
I just need to lose 5kg and eat to gain 2kg.

757
00:26:03,872 --> 00:26:05,242
The logic is very simple.

758
00:26:06,012 --> 00:26:07,312
I'll come back before we eat.

759
00:26:08,012 --> 00:26:11,182
(Moon Se Yoon's I want to lose 3kg)

760
00:26:12,312 --> 00:26:14,652
(He starts with a light run.)

761
00:26:16,152 --> 00:26:17,992
It's not lunch. It's a lunge.

762
00:26:18,352 --> 00:26:19,462
Lunge.

763
00:26:19,862 --> 00:26:21,192
"Lunch" is lunch in English.

764
00:26:21,892 --> 00:26:24,562
Lunges make you sweat and lose weight.

765
00:26:25,392 --> 00:26:27,761
This is a hardcore training.

766
00:26:27,762 --> 00:26:29,232
(Hardcore working to keep sweating)

767
00:26:32,472 --> 00:26:35,402
(He tries to push a bus with a capacity of 25 people.)

768
00:26:36,002 --> 00:26:37,842
(Struggling)

769
00:26:39,812 --> 00:26:42,282
(Moving up and down)

770
00:26:43,312 --> 00:26:46,182
(Se Yoon shows off his super power.)

771
00:26:48,352 --> 00:26:49,551
That must be enough to lose 500g, right?

772
00:26:49,552 --> 00:26:51,833
(All these exercises must be enough to lose 500g, right?)

773
00:26:53,092 --> 00:26:54,121
(Taking a break)

774
00:26:54,122 --> 00:26:55,622
Go away.

775
00:26:55,922 --> 00:26:58,532
I'm not meat.

776
00:26:59,162 --> 00:27:00,401
I'm not food.

777
00:27:00,402 --> 00:27:01,531
(The stray dog finds him just by sniffing.)

778
00:27:01,532 --> 00:27:02,702
I'm not some tasty meat.

779
00:27:03,032 --> 00:27:04,331
(You smell delicious.)

780
00:27:04,332 --> 00:27:05,972
The dog keeps smelling me.

781
00:27:06,502 --> 00:27:07,741
I'm not delicious meat.

782
00:27:07,742 --> 00:27:08,941
(While Se Yoon is busy trying to lose weight, )

783
00:27:08,942 --> 00:27:10,211
(what are the other members up to?)

784
00:27:10,212 --> 00:27:12,811
So this is where Ronaldo was born. He was born in Portugal.

785
00:27:12,812 --> 00:27:14,618
- This is...
- "Eat a bowl of red bean porridge."

786
00:27:14,642 --> 00:27:17,381
(Joon is exclusively helping Seon Ho.)

787
00:27:17,382 --> 00:27:19,181
He was born in Lisbon. Remember it as leasing a car.

788
00:27:19,182 --> 00:27:20,481
- It's so easy.
- Lisbon, Portugal.

789
00:27:20,482 --> 00:27:21,521
Easy, right?

790
