1034
00:34:37,752 --> 00:34:40,022
(A strong wave of pain hits them afterward.)

1035
00:34:40,692 --> 00:34:41,692
(Groaning)

1036
00:34:43,892 --> 00:34:45,892
- Hey. We did it.
- My gosh.

1037
00:34:46,192 --> 00:34:47,531
We stretched 15cm more.

1038
00:34:47,532 --> 00:34:49,231
(As he's so happy, he celebrates with an odd gesture.)

1039
00:34:49,232 --> 00:34:51,501
We stretched 15cm more.

1040
00:34:51,502 --> 00:34:54,442
(They paid a heavy price to push past their limit.)

1041
00:34:55,242 --> 00:34:57,072
- Everything is possible.
- We did it.

1042
00:34:58,512 --> 00:35:00,082
I think my pants are completely ripped.

1043
00:35:00,482 --> 00:35:01,742
Three ingredients.

1044
00:35:02,242 --> 00:35:03,411
We can pick three ingredients.

1045
00:35:03,412 --> 00:35:04,451
We can pick rice cakes, udon noodles,

1046
00:35:04,452 --> 00:35:05,481
- and cheese, right?
- Cheese.

1047
00:35:05,482 --> 00:35:06,981
- We can go with them.
- Yes.

1048
00:35:06,982 --> 00:35:08,121
- The trio.
- Rice cakes, noodles, and cheese.

1049
00:35:08,122 --> 00:35:09,122
Okay.

1050
00:35:09,123 --> 00:35:11,152
On the second mission, the official last dish...

1051
00:35:11,652 --> 00:35:13,861
of meals in Korea, fried rice, is at stake.

1052
00:35:13,862 --> 00:35:15,892
- We have to get this.
- We must eat fried rice.

1053
00:35:16,422 --> 00:35:18,692
Fried rice is at stake on the second mission.

1054
00:35:18,962 --> 00:35:20,701
Deliver Water Without Walking.

1055
00:35:20,702 --> 00:35:21,961
- Deliver Water Without Walking?
- Deliver...

1056
00:35:21,962 --> 00:35:24,372
One of the members will have a water cup on his head...

1057
00:35:24,702 --> 00:35:26,232
and get on top of the members.

1058
00:35:26,802 --> 00:35:29,642
The rest of the members will lie down and roll like logs.

1059
00:35:29,912 --> 00:35:32,641
That's how you move the mat, so you can deliver the water.

1060
00:35:32,642 --> 00:35:35,712
(The delivery zone, the water refill zone)

1061
00:35:36,082 --> 00:35:37,352
We have to roll?

1062
00:35:37,482 --> 00:35:39,411
- You will have ten minutes.
- That's a long time.

1063
00:35:39,412 --> 00:35:43,022
For every 500ml of water delivered, you get...

1064
00:35:43,322 --> 00:35:44,891
one serving of fried rice.

1065
00:35:44,892 --> 00:35:46,421
We must fill up 500ml? That's a lot.

1066
00:35:46,422 --> 00:35:47,698
- That's a lot of water.
- This is tough.

1067
00:35:47,722 --> 00:35:49,931
Then a lighter one should go on top.

1068
00:35:49,932 --> 00:35:50,932
- Right.
- That's the way to go.

1069
00:35:50,933 --> 00:35:52,091
Right? We don't have a choice.

1070
00:35:52,092 --> 00:35:53,161
You know your role, right?

1071
00:35:53,162 --> 00:35:55,278
Make sure to keep your balance, so the water doesn't spill out.

1072
00:35:55,302 --> 00:35:57,432
- Let's go.
- Yes. Let's do this.

1073
00:35:58,232 --> 00:36:00,741
(Seon Ho with the water cup sits on them first.)

1074
00:36:00,742 --> 00:36:01,802
I'll sit slowly.

1075
00:36:03,042 --> 00:36:04,411
- Grab this.
- You can do this, Seon Ho.

1076
00:36:04,412 --> 00:36:06,041
- Just be careful.
- We'll begin now.

1077
00:36:06,042 --> 00:36:07,911
Don't feel rushed. You can take your time.

1078
00:36:07,912 --> 00:36:09,741
- All right.
- I'm stable now.

1079
00:36:09,742 --> 00:36:10,781
- We should hurry.
- Okay.

1080
00:36:10,782 --> 00:36:11,881
- Get ready.
- We must go the other way too.

1081
00:36:11,882 --> 00:36:14,321
(The fried rice expedition sets off.)

1082
00:36:14,322 --> 00:36:15,881
(Will the 4 of them be able to roll smoothly?)

1083
00:36:15,882 --> 00:36:17,322
Jong Min, don't roll too hard.

1084
00:36:17,422 --> 00:36:20,562
(They're trying their best to roll.)

1085
00:36:21,062 --> 00:36:22,121
Jong Min, you must roll.

1086
00:36:22,122 --> 00:36:23,361
- Roll. Why aren't you rolling?
- I know that too.

1087
00:36:23,362 --> 00:36:24,931
- Why? All of us have to roll.
- Why aren't you rolling?

1088
00:36:24,932 --> 00:36:26,631
- I can't!
- Why not?

1089
00:36:26,632 --> 00:36:28,072
(They face a crisis from the start.)

1090
00:36:28,162 --> 00:36:29,661
I'm stuck.

1091
00:36:29,662 --> 00:36:31,031
Jong Min, you can't get up.

1092
00:36:31,032 --> 00:36:32,871
- I'm stuck.
- So try to roll more.

1093
00:36:32,872 --> 00:36:34,541
- He can't roll at all.
- Why aren't you moving?

1094
00:36:34,542 --> 00:36:35,641
One, two, three.

1095
00:36:35,642 --> 00:36:37,611
- I have to push Jong Min.
- Push me.

1096
00:36:37,612 --> 00:36:38,771
Push.

1097
00:36:38,772 --> 00:36:40,011
- Okay.
- Yes. Hang in there.

1098
00:36:40,012 --> 00:36:41,411
- Hang in there.
- There we go.

1099
00:36:41,412 --> 00:36:42,812
- Hang in there.
- This is it.

1100
00:36:42,942 --> 00:36:44,051
We got it. Roll like that.

1101
00:36:44,052 --> 00:36:45,082
It's working.

1102
00:36:46,052 --> 00:36:47,122
- Roll.
- Okay.

1103
00:36:47,552 --> 00:36:48,682
DinDin.

1104
00:36:49,182 --> 00:36:51,021
- Hang in there.
- Okay. We got this.

1105
00:36:51,022 --> 00:36:52,022
Is he rolling now?

1106
00:36:52,022 --> 00:36:53,022
(He's pushing with his massive body.)

1107
00:36:53,023 --> 00:36:55,261
(A graceful pose is a bonus.)

1108
00:36:55,262 --> 00:36:57,131
Great. DinDin is great at this.

1109
00:36:57,132 --> 00:36:58,161
Make sure your sides are touching.

1110
00:36:58,162 --> 00:36:59,932
DinDin is good. He's stable.

1111
00:37:00,832 --> 00:37:02,761
Great. This is it.

1112
00:37:02,762 --> 00:37:04,301
- Yes.
- One more time.

1113
00:37:04,302 --> 00:37:06,971
- I'm getting the hang of it.
- We got this. We're on a roll.

1114
00:37:06,972 --> 00:37:08,241
- We got it. We're nailing it.
- We're on a roll.

1115
00:37:08,242 --> 00:37:09,271
Are we there yet?

1116
00:37:09,272 --> 00:37:10,811
Yes. We're here. We're good.

1117
00:37:10,812 --> 00:37:12,041
Can you reach the water?

1118
00:37:12,042 --> 00:37:13,812
That's good. We have to go a little more.

1119
00:37:13,842 --> 00:37:15,242
That's good. I can reach the water.

1120
00:37:15,342 --> 00:37:16,582
- I'll get some water.
- Okay.

1121
00:37:16,882 --> 00:37:17,882
Oh, my gosh.

1122
00:37:17,883 --> 00:37:20,321
- Seon Ho.
- You can touch the cup.

1123
00:37:20,322 --> 00:37:22,282
- There you go. Keep your head up.
- Stop it.

1124
00:37:22,852 --> 00:37:23,891
Stop it.

1125
00:37:23,892 --> 00:37:25,168
(The water is spilling all over the ground.)

1126
00:37:25,192 --> 00:37:26,322
Get one more scoop.

1127
00:37:27,192 --> 00:37:28,192
One more scoop.

1128
00:37:28,962 --> 00:37:29,992
Higher. That's the spot.

1129
00:37:30,392 --> 00:37:31,761
- That's good.
- Let's go.

1130
00:37:31,762 --> 00:37:33,031
Jong Min, roll the other way.

1131
00:37:33,032 --> 00:37:34,132
- It's so cold.
- Let's go.

1132
00:37:34,462 --> 00:37:35,731
I'm the only one getting wet.

1133
00:37:35,732 --> 00:37:37,271
(He must come back to deliver the water safely now.)

1134
00:37:37,272 --> 00:37:39,131
- I'm not spilling any water now.
- Hey.

1135
00:37:39,132 --> 00:37:40,871
- I saw you guys. You're stable.
- He got the water?

1136
00:37:40,872 --> 00:37:42,948
- I'm not spilling any water.
- He's got a lot of water.

1137
00:37:42,972 --> 00:37:44,142
It's so stable now.

1138
00:37:44,912 --> 00:37:47,742
(Fighting a tough battle to win the fried rice)

1139
00:37:47,882 --> 00:37:50,311
It's going to work. With this, we can fill up 500ml.

1140
00:37:50,312 --> 00:37:51,312
- Hold on.
- This...

1141
00:37:51,782 --> 00:37:53,251
We got this. Yes.

1142
00:37:53,252 --> 00:37:55,021
- Over there.
- Pour it in right away.

1143
00:37:55,022 --> 00:37:56,082
- We're there.
- Not yet.

1144
00:37:57,292 --> 00:37:58,691
- I see a gap here.
- We got this.

1145
00:37:58,692 --> 00:37:59,721
- This is a big gap.
- We're here.

1146
00:37:59,722 --> 00:38:00,891
- Jong Min.
- Get closer.

1147
00:38:00,892 --> 00:38:03,222
- We must get closer. Wait. You...
- Get closer.

1148
00:38:03,392 --> 00:38:04,491
That's good. I saw it.

1149
00:38:04,492 --> 00:38:06,461
- Hold on.
- What do I do?

1150
00:38:06,462 --> 00:38:08,008
- You have to lower your head. No.
- Oh, no.

1151
00:38:08,032 --> 00:38:09,932
No. Keep holding your pose.

1152
00:38:10,032 --> 00:38:11,171
- Just a little bit.
- Lower your head.

1153
00:38:11,172 --> 00:38:12,971
- Lower your head there.
- That's the spot. Lower it.

1154
00:38:12,972 --> 00:38:14,972
- Lower your head. That's good.
- There you go.

1155
00:38:15,072 --> 00:38:16,601
- No!
- No!

1156
00:38:16,602 --> 00:38:17,771
- That's good.
- There you go.

1157
00:38:17,772 --> 00:38:21,611
(Oh, no!)

1158
00:38:21,612 --> 00:38:22,881
Move back.

1159
00:38:22,882 --> 00:38:27,721
(Seon Ho wastes half the water he spent 5 minutes delivering.)

1160
00:38:27,722 --> 00:38:29,251
- No!
- No!

1161
00:38:29,252 --> 00:38:31,122
(They're doomed.)

1162
00:38:31,692 --> 00:38:32,821
- Gosh, no.
- I can't see anything.

1163
00:38:32,822 --> 00:38:34,022
Let's go quickly.

1164
00:38:34,522 --> 00:38:35,622
- Let's go.
- Hey.

1165
00:38:35,692 --> 00:38:37,362
Come on, roll.

1166
00:38:37,492 --> 00:38:39,031
We can pick up the speed now.

1167
00:38:39,032 --> 00:38:40,701
- Roll.
- I think I can maintain my balance.

1168
00:38:40,702 --> 00:38:42,662
- There's no water. So speed up.
- Yes, speed up.

1169
00:38:43,262 --> 00:38:45,931
(No matter how cold it is, I can't be a burden on them.)

1170
00:38:45,932 --> 00:38:47,241
Come over here.

1171
00:38:47,242 --> 00:38:48,671
- Who's missing?
- Why aren't you coming?

1172
00:38:48,672 --> 00:38:50,272
- Gosh, who's missing here?
- Me.

1173
00:38:50,312 --> 00:38:51,371
Hurry.

1174
00:38:51,372 --> 00:38:52,472
(Groaning)

1175
00:38:53,142 --> 00:38:54,311
- Hey, not like that.
- I'm not there yet.

1176
00:38:54,312 --> 00:38:56,641
Jong Min, that's not good. Come closer to me.

1177
00:38:56,642 --> 00:38:57,762
(He's being a burden again.)

1178
00:38:58,112 --> 00:38:59,311
I might fall off.

1179
00:38:59,312 --> 00:39:01,251
- No.
- I told you to come closer.

1180
00:39:01,252 --> 00:39:02,622
- I got him.
- Okay.

1181
00:39:03,252 --> 00:39:04,652
You must push him.

1182
00:39:05,322 --> 00:39:08,262
(This time, Se Yoon pushes Jong Min with his foot to overcome it.)

1183
00:39:08,622 --> 00:39:10,892
- We've gotten faster.
- Okay. Come to me. Yes.

1184
00:39:11,032 --> 00:39:12,661
We suddenly speed up after Jong Min.

1185
00:39:12,662 --> 00:39:13,662
(They roll with perfect teamwork without Jong Min.)

1186
00:39:13,663 --> 00:39:15,002
You can get the water now, right?

1187
00:39:15,302 --> 00:39:16,502
Go ahead.

1188
00:39:17,332 --> 00:39:20,501
Don't do it on top of me. Darn it.

1189
00:39:20,502 --> 00:39:21,771
- Don't lower your head.
- My gosh. Hey.

1190
00:39:21,772 --> 00:39:22,892
(Jong Min is under Seon Ho.)

1191
00:39:23,402 --> 00:39:24,511
- Don't lower your head.
- My gosh. Hey.

1192
00:39:24,512 --> 00:39:27,112
(Splashing the weakest player with water to improve)

1193
00:39:27,442 --> 00:39:28,511
- That's good.
- Okay.

1194
00:39:28,512 --> 00:39:30,081
- Let's go. No.
- One more scoop.

1195
00:39:30,082 --> 00:39:32,351
- One more scoop.
- Let's go. No. No more...

1196
00:39:32,352 --> 00:39:33,921
(Getting a cold shower)

1197
00:39:33,922 --> 00:39:35,182
- Yes.
- My gosh.

1198
00:39:35,282 --> 00:39:37,721
- That's good. Let's go.
- One more scoop.

1199
00:39:37,722 --> 00:39:38,922
No!

1200
00:39:39,392 --> 00:39:40,761
Seon Ho. Lift your head.

1201
00:39:40,762 --> 00:39:41,861
- Wait.
- Lift your head.

1202
00:39:41,862 --> 00:39:43,191
- Hey, lean back.
- My gosh.

1203
00:39:43,192 --> 00:39:45,391
- Lift your head.
- Don't do it.

1204
00:39:45,392 --> 00:39:46,561
- Gosh, I'm wet now.
- That's great.

1205
00:39:46,562 --> 00:39:47,562
Let's go.

1206
00:39:48,232 --> 00:39:49,301
Let's go, Seon Ho.

1207
00:39:49,302 --> 00:39:50,771
- I'm wet.
- Jong Min, go to the other side.

1208
00:39:50,772 --> 00:39:52,231
- Kick him.
- Jong Min, you have to roll.

1209
00:39:52,232 --> 00:39:53,232
Okay.

1210
00:39:54,002 --> 00:39:56,041
- Get him.
- Lift him and push.

1211
00:39:56,042 --> 00:39:57,348
- Lift him up.
- Roll and take him.

1212
00:39:57,372 --> 00:39:59,011
- Hold on. Se Yoon, roll.
- Hey.

1213
00:39:59,012 --> 00:40:00,012
(Hopefully, they can deliver the water.)

1214
00:40:00,013 --> 00:40:01,481
(Staggering)

1215
00:40:01,482 --> 00:40:02,812
No. Lift your head.

1216
00:40:02,842 --> 00:40:04,351
Keep your head up. Yes, that's it.

1217
00:40:04,352 --> 00:40:05,981
- That's it.
- Take your time.

1218
00:40:05,982 --> 00:40:08,122
- Okay. Lift him.
- To the right. Wait. Yes.

1219
00:40:08,422 --> 00:40:09,551
Here we go again.

1220
00:40:09,552 --> 00:40:11,651
- Okay. We got it.
- We got it. We're here.

1221
00:40:11,652 --> 00:40:13,091
- We're almost here.
- We're here.

1222
00:40:13,092 --> 00:40:14,391
- Seon Ho, we're here.
- Do I have a lot of water left?

1223
00:40:14,392 --> 00:40:15,461
- Yes.
- Yes. You have a lot of water.

1224
00:40:15,462 --> 00:40:16,491
Seon Ho, wait.

1225
00:40:16,492 --> 00:40:18,092
- Wait.
- You just need to pour it well.

1226
00:40:18,162 --> 00:40:20,861
(He must now pour their precious water accurately into the bucket.)

1227
00:40:20,862 --> 00:40:22,201
- This is it. Bow down.
- Yes.

1228
00:40:22,202 --> 00:40:23,901
Bow down slowly.

1229
00:40:23,902 --> 00:40:25,071
- I'll push you back.
- Slowly.

1230
00:40:25,072 --> 00:40:26,531
- Keep it just like that.
- I'll push you back.

1231
00:40:26,532 --> 00:40:28,842
- Keep it just like that.
- Seon Ho, move your head back.

1232
00:40:29,342 --> 00:40:31,411
(Seon Ho is pouring carefully as DinDin adjust the location.)

1233
00:40:31,412 --> 00:40:32,842
Slowly.

1234
00:40:33,412 --> 00:40:35,111
Pour everything out. Go ahead.

1235
00:40:35,112 --> 00:40:36,781
Go ahead.

1236
00:40:36,782 --> 00:40:38,381
- Keep pouring.
- This is no joke!

1237
00:40:38,382 --> 00:40:40,111
- Okay.
- There you go.

1238
00:40:40,112 --> 00:40:41,382
- That's good.
- That's good.

1239
00:40:41,752 --> 00:40:45,122
(This time, he delivers the water without any mistake.)

1240
00:40:45,492 --> 00:40:46,492
Good work.

1241
00:40:46,492 --> 00:40:47,492
(They deliver the water without walking.)

1242
00:40:47,493 --> 00:40:49,621
Seriously. The water hit my face and it was freezing.

1243
00:40:49,622 --> 00:40:51,491
It went over 500ml.

1244
00:40:51,492 --> 00:40:52,731
So...

1245
00:40:52,732 --> 00:40:54,131
The four of us can have a spoonful each.

1246
00:40:54,132 --> 00:40:56,931
You won one serving of fried rice.

1247
00:40:56,932 --> 00:40:58,101
- That's better than nothing.
- What a relief.

1248
00:40:58,102 --> 00:40:59,271
- Imagine if we failed this one too.
- We somehow managed.

1249
00:40:59,272 --> 00:41:00,701
We couldn't have made another trip.

1250
00:41:00,702 --> 00:41:02,171
Winning one serving was the best we could've done.

1251
00:41:02,172 --> 00:41:03,612
- So it means we succeeded.
- Yes.

1252
00:41:04,242 --> 00:41:07,541
We'll do the last mission at another location.

1253
00:41:07,542 --> 00:41:08,642
- Okay.
- Okay.

1254
00:41:08,982 --> 00:41:10,011
- What's this?
- Everyone.

1255
00:41:10,012 --> 00:41:11,911
We put a lot of effort into the last one.

1256
00:41:11,912 --> 00:41:13,112
- They did?
- All right.

1257
00:41:13,482 --> 00:41:15,081
- Okay.
- Gosh, it's cold.

1258
00:41:15,082 --> 00:41:17,792
- Bring it in.
- What's going on?

1259
00:41:18,451 --> 00:41:20,421
- What is it? What's coming in?
- What?

1260
00:41:20,581 --> 00:41:23,251
- What's that?
- What is it?

1261
00:41:23,551 --> 00:41:25,320
(A dump truck emerges out.)

1262
00:41:25,321 --> 00:41:26,420
A truck is coming in.

1263
00:41:26,421 --> 00:41:28,091
Oh, my. This is on a different scale.

1264
00:41:29,291 --> 00:41:30,630
Is this a major project?

1265
00:41:30,631 --> 00:41:31,861
(Is he scared?)

1266
00:41:32,091 --> 00:41:36,871
(The dump truck is slowly approaching the members.)

1267
00:41:36,971 --> 00:41:39,200
- How much can the truck carry?
- They got a 25t truck.

1268
00:41:39,201 --> 00:41:40,701
- Right.
- It can carry 25.5t?

1269
00:41:41,001 --> 00:41:42,601
Do we have to survive getting hit by it?

1270
00:41:43,411 --> 00:41:44,411
What?

1271
00:41:44,412 --> 00:41:47,140
(The 8-wheeled dump truck is backing up toward them.)

1272
00:41:47,141 --> 00:41:48,210
What's up with the grand scale?

1273
00:41:48,211 --> 00:41:49,380
The scale... My gosh.

1274
00:41:49,381 --> 00:41:50,857
- I guess our mission is in there.
- What's this?

1275
00:41:50,881 --> 00:41:52,641
- Right. My gosh.
- What's this? I'm scared!

1276
00:41:53,681 --> 00:41:56,051
I didn't know it was this hard to win dakgalbi for dinner.

1277
00:41:56,451 --> 00:41:59,091
I won't eat it. Fine. I won't have dinner.

1278
00:41:59,961 --> 00:42:01,920
The famous dish of Chuncheon, dakgalbi, is at stake...

1279
00:42:01,921 --> 00:42:03,241
on the last round of the mission.

1280
00:42:03,761 --> 00:42:05,430
It's called Hang-Tight Quiz Show.

1281
00:42:05,431 --> 00:42:07,030
(Round 3 of the Dinner Game, Hang-Tight Quiz Show)

1282
00:42:07,031 --> 00:42:09,101
- Hang-Tight?
- We're doing a quiz show on it?

1283
00:42:09,331 --> 00:42:11,070
You'll get on the back of the dump truck...

1284
00:42:11,071 --> 00:42:13,100
which will get steeper as time goes on.

1285
00:42:13,101 --> 00:42:16,741
You must correctly answer the questions without falling off.

1286
00:42:16,841 --> 00:42:17,841
We can just hang tight.

1287
00:42:17,842 --> 00:42:19,040
The quiz will continue...

1288
00:42:19,041 --> 00:42:21,641
until you answer five questions correctly.

1289
00:42:21,841 --> 00:42:22,980
I see. Okay.

1290
00:42:22,981 --> 00:42:25,181
I'll present one question every minute.

1291
00:42:25,981 --> 00:42:26,981
That's tough.

1292
00:42:26,982 --> 00:42:28,350
We'll have to stay on it for five minutes.

1293
00:42:28,351 --> 00:42:29,520
No, until you answer five questions correctly.

1294
00:42:29,521 --> 00:42:30,791
There's no way we can do that.

1295
00:42:30,991 --> 00:42:34,291
You only get one try to answer the question.

1296
00:42:34,621 --> 00:42:36,960
After five correct answers, the number of members...

1297
00:42:36,961 --> 00:42:39,860
still on the dump truck will equal...

1298
00:42:39,861 --> 00:42:42,001
the number of dakgalbi servings for your dinner.

1299
00:42:42,731 --> 00:42:45,970
(The last mission is crucial as meat is at stake on it.)

1300
00:42:45,971 --> 00:42:48,041
- Let's try it.
- Se Yoon can't eat anyway.

1301
00:42:48,241 --> 00:42:49,270
Why can't I eat it?

1302
00:42:49,271 --> 00:42:50,440
I lost 1kg.

1303
00:42:50,441 --> 00:42:51,587
(How many servings will they be able to win?)

1304
00:42:51,611 --> 00:42:53,710
There's nothing to hang onto here.

1305
00:42:53,711 --> 00:42:54,840
(Getting on the truck)

1306
00:42:54,841 --> 00:42:56,251
I don't see anything we can grab.

1307
00:42:56,381 --> 00:42:57,541
There's nothing to grab here.

1308
00:42:57,981 --> 00:42:59,281
There's nothing to grab!

1309
00:42:59,421 --> 00:43:01,497
If we only hang on with our arms, we'll fall off no matter what.

1310
00:43:01,521 --> 00:43:03,190
We need to fix our legs somewhere.

1311
00:43:03,191 --> 00:43:04,991
We need to hang onto it like this.

1312
00:43:05,491 --> 00:43:06,760
- Right. Like that.
- Yes.

1313
00:43:06,761 --> 00:43:08,221
(His posture looks very unstable.)

1314
00:43:08,521 --> 00:43:10,461
Actually, I'm going to be on the edge.

1315
00:43:10,631 --> 00:43:11,891
Gosh, it's so slippery.

1316
00:43:12,731 --> 00:43:13,930
You'll slide off right away.

1317
00:43:13,931 --> 00:43:15,477
(Counterintuitive thinking, sitting on the edge)

1318
00:43:15,501 --> 00:43:16,801
We can push each other's feet.

1319
00:43:17,331 --> 00:43:18,400
We can push each other's feet.

1320
00:43:18,401 --> 00:43:20,047
- But we can slide off together.
- Let's try it.

1321
00:43:20,071 --> 00:43:23,041
- We might slide off together.
- We can push each other like this.

1322
00:43:23,311 --> 00:43:24,591
- This isn't a bad idea.
- What?

1323
00:43:24,671 --> 00:43:26,711
- Jong Min.
- We won't even try to save him?

1324
00:43:26,911 --> 00:43:28,011
Jong Min.

1325
00:43:28,111 --> 00:43:29,410
You have to come to the middle.

1326
00:43:29,411 --> 00:43:31,750
(How long can we last on the truck?)

1327
00:43:31,751 --> 00:43:33,520
We'll start the mission!

1328
00:43:33,521 --> 00:43:35,680
- Okay.
- Could you speak louder?

1329
00:43:35,681 --> 00:43:37,050
What's going on? Why is it moving?

1330
00:43:37,051 --> 00:43:41,321
(The truck's ramp starts moving up.)

1331
00:43:41,361 --> 00:43:42,431
(What's going on?)

1332
00:43:43,061 --> 00:43:44,430
- We must be starting.
- My gosh.

1333
00:43:44,431 --> 00:43:45,590
(The ramp is quickly getting steeper.)

1334
00:43:45,591 --> 00:43:47,300
- Oh, my.
- What? Are they serious?

1335
00:43:47,301 --> 00:43:49,570
We didn't start the quiz yet. Why are you moving the ramp?

1336
00:43:49,571 --> 00:43:50,630
(They start to see the ground more clearly.)

1337
00:43:50,631 --> 00:43:52,100
- This is the starting position.
- My gosh. Really?

1338
00:43:52,101 --> 00:43:54,171
- This is the starting position?
- This isn't bad.

1339
00:43:54,401 --> 00:43:56,910
We must maintain our balance. It's all about our balance.

1340
00:43:56,911 --> 00:43:58,111
- Okay.
- Shift your weight.

1341
00:43:58,141 --> 00:43:59,610
Listen carefully.

1342
00:43:59,611 --> 00:44:00,681
- Yes.
- Yes.

1343
00:44:01,541 --> 00:44:03,251
Here's the first question.

1344
00:44:03,751 --> 00:44:06,451
I'll play a scene from a drama.

1345
00:44:06,681 --> 00:44:08,150
Listen to the scene...

1346
00:44:08,151 --> 00:44:09,590
- and guess the title of the drama.
- Okay.

1347
00:44:09,591 --> 00:44:12,291
- I'm good at this.
- Play the scene!

1348
00:44:13,161 --> 00:44:18,061
(Here comes the question.)

1349
00:44:18,431 --> 00:44:23,401
(All of a sudden, they hear someone laughing.)

1350
00:44:25,231 --> 00:44:26,300
- What?
- What?

1351
00:44:26,301 --> 00:44:27,370
- There weren't any lines.
- You can...

1352
00:44:27,371 --> 00:44:29,870
You can discuss it among yourselves. You only have one chance...

1353
00:44:29,871 --> 00:44:31,540
- to answer it.
- I bet it's a historical drama.

1354
00:44:31,541 --> 00:44:32,610
- It sounded like Joon's laugh.
- It must be a historical drama.

1355
00:44:32,611 --> 00:44:34,380
- Wasn't that Joon's laugh?
- Wasn't that your laugh?

1356
00:44:34,381 --> 00:44:35,610
- Didn't it sound like his laugh?
- Actually...

1357
00:44:35,611 --> 00:44:39,081
(Was it Joon's boisterous laugh?)

1358
00:44:39,181 --> 00:44:40,250
- Didn't it sound like his laugh?
- Actually,

1359
00:44:40,251 --> 00:44:41,720
it sounded like my laugh, but it wasn't mine.

1360
00:44:41,721 --> 00:44:43,090
- I can recognize my laugh.
- Yes.

1361
00:44:43,091 --> 00:44:44,091
- He would know.
- Right.

1362
00:44:44,092 --> 00:44:45,692
- It's a historical drama, right?
- Yes.

1363
00:44:46,561 --> 00:44:48,520
- He sounded like Sung Dong Il.
- Sung Dong Il.

1364
00:44:48,521 --> 00:44:50,430
- Sung Dong Il.
- Can you play it again?

1365
00:44:50,431 --> 00:44:51,490
One more time.

1366
00:44:51,491 --> 00:44:55,901
(We'll play it one more time.)

1367
00:44:56,901 --> 00:44:58,771
- It's him.
- It's Sung Dong Il, isn't it?

1368
00:44:59,301 --> 00:45:00,970
- Let's go with "The Slave Hunters."
- I don't think that's it.

1369
00:45:00,971 --> 00:45:02,300
- Let's go with it.
- Let's just do it.

1370
00:45:02,301 --> 00:45:03,340
- Okay. Let's do it.
- Should we?

1371
00:45:03,341 --> 00:45:04,540
- One, two, three.
- It might be right.

1372
00:45:04,541 --> 00:45:05,610
- "The Slave Hunters."
- "The Slave Hunters."

1373
00:45:05,611 --> 00:45:06,711
It was Sung Dong Il.

1374
00:45:06,881 --> 00:45:07,881
- "The Slave Hunters?"
- Yes.

1375
00:45:07,882 --> 00:45:09,450
- It was Sung Dong Il.
- I guess we're wrong.

1376
00:45:09,451 --> 00:45:10,510
- We got it. It's him.
- That's correct.

1377
00:45:10,511 --> 00:45:13,051
("The Slave Hunters")

1378
00:45:13,281 --> 00:45:14,620
(Jong Min's guess was right.)

1379
00:45:14,621 --> 00:45:16,621
- You were right.
- How did you figure that out?

1380
00:45:18,551 --> 00:45:20,960
(The superb supporting character in "The Slave Hunters")

1381
00:45:20,961 --> 00:45:23,361
(The laugh belongs to Sung Dong Il.)

1382
00:45:23,991 --> 00:45:25,691
(They only get to celebrate briefly.)

1383
00:45:25,761 --> 00:45:27,730
- Why are you tilting the ramp?
- Push.

1384
00:45:27,731 --> 00:45:29,570
(As it's been 1 minute, the ramp gets steeper.)

1385
00:45:29,571 --> 00:45:31,230
- Why are you tilting it?
- What's going on? What?

1386
00:45:31,231 --> 00:45:32,231
(Utter chaos)

1387
00:45:32,232 --> 00:45:34,577
- Hey, don't bring me down with you.
- What's going on? Let's hurry.

1388
00:45:34,601 --> 00:45:35,921
I don't need any support for now.

1389
00:45:36,371 --> 00:45:38,041
You know what? We can push here.

1390
00:45:38,541 --> 00:45:40,240
- No. Right here.
- No. Hold me.

1391
00:45:40,241 --> 00:45:41,280
Push your feet. Yes.

1392
00:45:41,281 --> 00:45:44,080
- It will be given in a minute.
- I'll move aside for you.

1393
00:45:44,081 --> 00:45:45,650
- I think it's going up again.
- No.

1394
00:45:45,651 --> 00:45:46,651
No, it's not going up.

1395
00:45:46,651 --> 00:45:47,651
Then what's wrong?

1396
00:45:47,652 --> 00:45:49,621
- You're comfortable now, right?
- Yes, totally.

1397
00:45:50,521 --> 00:45:52,150
Hey, stay still comfortably for now...

1398
00:45:52,151 --> 00:45:53,890
and hold out when it goes up.

1399
00:45:53,891 --> 00:45:55,320
- What's wrong with me?
- What's going on? I think...

1400
00:45:55,321 --> 00:45:57,241
- I'm going to slide down.
- Isn't it endurable?

1401
00:45:57,691 --> 00:45:58,691
Hold out.

1402
00:45:58,692 --> 00:45:59,730
(Grabbing Joon's leg)

1403
00:45:59,731 --> 00:46:01,300
Jong Min, wait. We might both slide down.

1404
00:46:01,301 --> 00:46:02,330
(Joon refuses to help him.)

1405
00:46:02,331 --> 00:46:04,231
I think we're okay for now.

1406
00:46:04,731 --> 00:46:06,240
What are you doing right now?

1407
00:46:06,241 --> 00:46:08,601
Okay, Jong Min. Hold me. I'll hold out.

1408
00:46:08,841 --> 00:46:10,171
I'll hold out. Grab it.

1409
00:46:10,211 --> 00:46:11,710
- Don't waste your energy now.
- Okay.

1410
00:46:11,711 --> 00:46:12,810
(He holds out grabbing Joon's clothes.)

1411
00:46:12,811 --> 00:46:15,440
You have to guess the title of a drama again.

1412
00:46:15,441 --> 00:46:16,951
- A drama?
- Yes.

1413
00:46:17,111 --> 00:46:19,221
Let them hear the question.

1414
00:46:19,921 --> 00:46:22,050
I'm annoying when I act pretty, right?

1415
00:46:22,051 --> 00:46:24,820
(I'm annoying when I act pretty, right?)

1416
00:46:24,821 --> 00:46:26,590
- "Fight For My Way."
- "Fight For My Way."

1417
00:46:26,591 --> 00:46:28,020
- "Fight For My Way."
- "Fight For My Way."

1418
00:46:28,021 --> 00:46:29,630
- "Fight For My Way."
- "Fight For My Way."

1419
00:46:29,631 --> 00:46:31,307
- "Fight For My Way" is...
- It's the correct answer.

1420
00:46:31,331 --> 00:46:32,830
- correct.
- Did you know that?

1421
00:46:32,831 --> 00:46:34,831
- "Fight For My Way" aired on KBS.
- That's right.

1422
00:46:35,731 --> 00:46:39,871
(The drama that propelled Actress Kim Ji Won to stardom)

1423
00:46:40,101 --> 00:46:44,370
(The legendary scene from the drama "Fight For My Way")

1424
00:46:44,371 --> 00:46:45,940
"Fight For My Way" aired on KBS.

1425
00:46:45,941 --> 00:46:47,680
(As soon as they got the answer, the incline gets steeper.)

1426
00:46:47,681 --> 00:46:49,510
(It's going up.)

1427
00:46:49,511 --> 00:46:51,151
Hey, don't push me. Don't touch me.

1428
00:46:52,881 --> 00:46:54,681
We're okay for now.

1429
00:46:54,981 --> 00:46:56,521
- We're okay now.
- Don't worry.

1430
00:46:56,751 --> 00:46:58,551
- I'll step on it.
- We're doing okay so far.

1431
00:46:58,821 --> 00:46:59,891
I'm totally fine.

1432
00:47:00,091 --> 00:47:01,191
Hold on.

1433
00:47:01,621 --> 00:47:02,631
This is good.

1434
00:47:03,031 --> 00:47:04,231
Nice. That's great.

1435
00:47:05,491 --> 00:47:06,500
Nice. That's great.

1436
00:47:06,501 --> 00:47:07,731
(I used to be a dance singer.)

1437
00:47:07,961 --> 00:47:08,961
(Pushing his leg)

1438
00:47:12,741 --> 00:47:15,141
(Sliding)

1439
00:47:16,211 --> 00:47:17,940
- Oh, no. Wait.
- I'm so sorry.

1440
00:47:17,941 --> 00:47:18,941
Oh, gosh.

1441
00:47:18,941 --> 00:47:19,941
(I almost fell.)

1442
00:47:19,942 --> 00:47:21,011
This time,

1443
00:47:21,581 --> 00:47:23,910
listen to the theme song of a TV show...

1444
00:47:23,911 --> 00:47:26,880
- and guess the TV show.
- Okay.

1445
00:47:26,881 --> 00:47:28,321
- Se Yoon is good at this.
- Got it.

1446
00:47:28,351 --> 00:47:29,521
Play the music, please.

1447
00:47:30,951 --> 00:47:34,921
(Which TV show's theme song is this?)

1448
00:47:35,891 --> 00:47:38,561
- This is a news show.
- It's a sports news show.

1449
00:47:38,631 --> 00:47:40,637
- Right. I think so too.
- It's a sports news show.

1450
00:47:40,661 --> 00:47:42,701
It's a sports news show.

1451
00:47:44,371 --> 00:47:46,170
This is definitely the theme song of a sports news show.

1452
00:47:46,171 --> 00:47:47,270
That's what it sounds like, but...

1453
00:47:47,271 --> 00:47:49,310
- "KBS Sports News."
- "KBS Sports News?"

1454
00:47:49,311 --> 00:47:50,751
Isn't the title "Sports Highlights?"

1455
00:47:50,811 --> 00:47:58,051
(The music does suit a sports news show perfectly.)

1456
00:47:58,251 --> 00:47:59,280
We'll answer now.

1457
00:47:59,281 --> 00:48:00,820
"KBS Sports News."

1458
00:48:00,821 --> 00:48:02,621
"KBS Sports News."

1459
00:48:02,721 --> 00:48:04,920
"KBS Sports News" is...

1460
00:48:04,921 --> 00:48:05,921
incorrect.

1461
00:48:05,951 --> 00:48:07,021
- What?
- The answer is...

1462
00:48:08,221 --> 00:48:09,930
(The answer is...)

1463
00:48:09,931 --> 00:48:13,431
("Earth Expedition.")

1464
00:48:13,801 --> 00:48:15,101
What? What's going on?

1465
00:48:15,231 --> 00:48:17,201
I'll hold you if you look like you'll fall.

1466
00:48:17,831 --> 00:48:18,900
It's hard now.

1467
00:48:18,901 --> 00:48:20,000
This is too steep.

1468
00:48:20,001 --> 00:48:21,077
(They can feel the incline.)

1469
00:48:21,101 --> 00:48:22,170
It's too steep.

1470
00:48:22,171 --> 00:48:24,571
(The upper end is as high as a tall tree now.)

1471
00:48:24,671 --> 00:48:26,110
- I don't think I can hold out.
- It's really unstable.

1472
00:48:26,111 --> 00:48:28,141
I can't hold you. You might slide down with me.

1473
00:48:28,411 --> 00:48:30,210
- You're okay now, right?
- It's slippery.

1474
00:48:30,211 --> 00:48:31,810
- I'm holding out with my arms.
- Do you have enough space there?

1475
00:48:31,811 --> 00:48:33,450
- Is it hard to hold out?
- Let go of my hand for a bit.

1476
00:48:33,451 --> 00:48:35,127
It's hard to hold out at every spot except for where you are.

1477
00:48:35,151 --> 00:48:36,791
We're holding out using our arm strength.

1478
00:48:37,091 --> 00:48:38,151
- No.
- Oh, gosh.

1479
00:48:38,351 --> 00:48:40,390
Jong Min, I'm just trying... Hold on.

1480
00:48:40,391 --> 00:48:41,491
I'm just trying to survive.

1481
00:48:43,591 --> 00:48:45,590
(Jong Min barely holds out stepping on Se Yoon's leg.)

1482
00:48:45,591 --> 00:48:47,761
- Don't do that.
- Jong Min, hold me.

1483
00:48:48,931 --> 00:48:50,071
Jong Min, hold me.

1484
00:48:51,201 --> 00:48:54,371
(He grabs DinDin.)

1485
00:48:54,501 --> 00:48:58,371
(While Jong Min survived with DinDin's help...)

1486
00:48:58,441 --> 00:49:01,610
Like last time, listen to the theme song of a TV show...

1487
00:49:01,611 --> 00:49:03,451
and guess the title of the TV show.

1488
00:49:03,981 --> 00:49:06,721
- Play the music, please.
- Hurry up.

1489
00:49:07,421 --> 00:49:08,620
We must hold out.

1490
00:49:08,621 --> 00:49:10,221
(The music plays.)

1491
00:49:10,591 --> 00:49:12,090
(Oh, this song...)

1492
00:49:12,091 --> 00:49:14,320
- Is it "Live Info Show?"
- I think it's "Live Info Show."

1493
00:49:14,321 --> 00:49:15,321
"Live Info Show."

1494
00:49:16,131 --> 00:49:17,731
It's a show like "Live Info Show."

1495
00:49:17,791 --> 00:49:18,960
I don't think so.

1496
00:49:18,961 --> 00:49:20,900
- It's not "Morning Forum," is it?
- It's not "Morning Forum."

1497
00:49:20,901 --> 00:49:23,021
Hold on. My hand is getting weaker. Give me a second.

1498
00:49:23,771 --> 00:49:25,370
- Oh, no.
- Hey.

1499
00:49:25,371 --> 00:49:26,400
- Hey, are you okay?
- Oh, gosh.

1500
00:49:26,401 --> 00:49:27,940
Hey, stop it. You might make us both fall.

1501
00:49:27,941 --> 00:49:29,810
(Se Yoon and Jong Min slide down being entangled with each other.)

1502
00:49:29,811 --> 00:49:31,740
Don't bring me down with you. Hey.

1503
00:49:31,741 --> 00:49:34,881
- Hey, because of you...
- Take off your gloves.

1504
00:49:35,741 --> 00:49:36,910
- Don't hold me.
- Okay.

1505
00:49:36,911 --> 00:49:38,950
- I'll try lying down on my belly.
- Can you hurry up?

1506
00:49:38,951 --> 00:49:40,280
I think I should use my belly. I'll try it.

1507
00:49:40,281 --> 00:49:41,961
- Just hurry up, will you?
- It's working.

1508
00:49:42,181 --> 00:49:44,290
My belly is stopping me from sliding down.

1509
00:49:44,291 --> 00:49:45,820
- That's so funny.
- I'm using my belly.

1510
00:49:45,821 --> 00:49:47,990
(Fascinated)

1511
00:49:47,991 --> 00:49:49,360
- That seems like a good idea.
- Do you think you can come up?

1512
00:49:49,361 --> 00:49:51,690
