2607
01:31:43,076 --> 01:31:44,076
I think so.

2608
01:31:44,077 --> 01:31:46,045
We both failed.

2609
01:31:46,046 --> 01:31:47,046
I know.

2610
01:31:47,116 --> 01:31:48,592
Only those who failed are sleeping indoors.

2611
01:31:48,616 --> 01:31:49,975
It's you and me again.

2612
01:31:49,976 --> 01:31:51,986
I know. I feel bad for them.

2613
01:31:52,346 --> 01:31:54,456
- They will sleep well, right?
- Sure.

2614
01:31:54,986 --> 01:31:56,555
And it's not...

2615
01:31:56,556 --> 01:31:58,956
- as cold as we thought it would be.
- Really?

2616
01:31:59,286 --> 01:32:00,555
It's quite cold.

2617
01:32:00,556 --> 01:32:01,595
(No, it's cold.)

2618
01:32:01,596 --> 01:32:03,156
- It's...
- It's cold.

2619
01:32:03,456 --> 01:32:05,025
This isn't so bad, though.

2620
01:32:05,026 --> 01:32:06,126
Right.

2621
01:32:06,826 --> 01:32:09,666
(The current temperature is minus 6°C.)

2622
01:32:09,796 --> 01:32:11,236
It's not windy.

2623
01:32:11,606 --> 01:32:13,306
It's better because it's not windy.

2624
01:32:13,776 --> 01:32:15,836
So I ended up here.

2625
01:32:16,106 --> 01:32:17,905
You came here after losing 3kg.

2626
01:32:17,906 --> 01:32:19,676
And DinDin came here after jumping well.

2627
01:32:20,246 --> 01:32:21,246
(They end up sleeping outdoors after succeeding in the missions.)

2628
01:32:21,247 --> 01:32:24,215
Seriously, I can't stop thinking about the dakgalbi.

2629
01:32:24,216 --> 01:32:25,885
(I didn't starve myself for this.)

2630
01:32:25,886 --> 01:32:27,046
Was it good?

2631
01:32:27,156 --> 01:32:29,385
- It was really good.
- It was delicious.

2632
01:32:29,386 --> 01:32:30,455
Seriously?

2633
01:32:30,456 --> 01:32:31,586
It was really good.

2634
01:32:31,756 --> 01:32:34,125
I shouldn't start the new year like this.

2635
01:32:34,126 --> 01:32:35,806
(This isn't a good start to the new year.)

2636
01:32:36,096 --> 01:32:38,266
Do you know what's good here?

2637
01:32:38,426 --> 01:32:40,566
- What?
- Drawing Groups.

2638
01:32:40,666 --> 01:32:42,766
- Right.
- I think Jong Min...

2639
01:32:42,996 --> 01:32:44,135
will come at 3pm.

2640
01:32:44,136 --> 01:32:45,206
I know, right?

2641
01:32:45,436 --> 01:32:48,276
Next time... I really don't want to say this,

2642
01:32:49,076 --> 01:32:50,575
